	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I've now done the quests for 3 pieces of crafted, and this was by far the easiest (boots, arms, legs). Najena is *never* crowded, and the Trazdon side of the dungeon can be completely controlled by a level 27+ warrior and an equivalent level *anything* that can heal.<BR>
<BR>
The circlet is dropped by Trazdon, a necromancer that spawns near the Bonecrack room. The Trazdon spot sometimes has a Magician placeholder spawn that you have to kill. The spawn is completely predictable on an 18-19 minute cycle. <BR>
<BR>
I had bad luck -- I had to kill 9 Trazdons and 7 placeholders over the course of a couple days. Another group got 3 circlets in a row. You never know -- the average seems to be 1 in 3 drop.<BR>
<BR>
The beauty of this is that the Ogre Captain (drops large bronze, guaranteed, every time) is on a similar 18-20 minute cycle, as is Bonecrack (who drops a Barbed Leather Whip and Leering Mask). A group of two high 20s can work all 3 easily -- I held all 3 for 3 hours with a 29th cleric and 2 hours with a 27th druid. I got a whip, a dark circlet, several bronze pieces that I gave to an Ogre buddy, and lots of bronze weapons.<BR>
<BR>
Do this quest, it's easier than Permafrost, and it's a lot of fun.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Kindsun Stormpainter<BR>
Warrior of the Stormguard, Tribunal Chapter<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
